			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coal tar is a byproduct derived from the coking, coal gasification or liquefaction processes of bituminous coal. It is a complex mixture of phenols, polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAHs), and heterocyclic compounds, characterized by its black, viscous appearance. Coal tar is processed for the production of tar-based products, compliance with industry standards, and may be used in medical treatments, roofing applications, or as a base for coatings and sealants. The flow of coal tar in the LCA includes details on its treatment, quality, usage, its educt being bituminous coal, and whether it is supplied as a production or consumption mix, potentially 'to consumer' or 'at plant', with details on each aspect separated by commas.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">煤焦油是从烟煤的炼焦、煤气化或液化过程中产生的副产品。它是由酚类、多环芳烃（PAHs）和杂环化合物组成的复杂混合物，特点是黑色、粘稠。煤焦油在遵循行业标准的情况下进行加工，以生产基于焦油的产品，并可用于医疗治疗、屋顶施工或作为涂层和密封剂的基体。生命周期评估中的煤焦油流动包括其处理、质量、用途、原料为烟煤等详细说明，并指出其是否作为生产或消费混合物供应，可能是‘给消费者’或‘在工厂’，并逐一列出各方面的细节。</common:generalComment>
